ton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527218\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527218\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 30, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ene1665703131995.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ene1665703131995.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ene1665703131995.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ene1665703131995\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ene1665703131995__ugetbind_403275\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Get the internal bind name of a Uniface field.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"ene1665703131995__topic_d120203e1_d120204e1_d120205e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104ene1665703131995_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"ene1665703131995__codeblock_iqb_zvz_zvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">int ugetbind (unsigned char*fieldname,unsigned char*bindname);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ene1665703131995__topic_d85517e1_d85518e1_d85519e1_d85520e1_d85521e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1017046e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"ene1665703131995__parml_lwb_1wz_zvb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">fieldname</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Name of a field in your component. To resolve ambiguity, you can qualify the\n                  field name with an entity name, for example, <var class=\"keyword varname\">fieldname</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">.</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">entity</var>.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">bindname</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">String that receives the internal bind name. This buffer should be at least 6\n                  bytes in length.</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ene1665703131995__topic_d85522e1_d85523e1_d85524e1_d85525e1_d85526e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1017046e99\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ene1665703131995__table_d14861e1_d14862e1_d14863e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by ugetbind</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ene1665703131995__table_d14861e1_d14862e1_d14863e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ene1665703131995__table_d14861e1_d14862e1_d14863e1__entry__2\">Meaning</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ene1665703131995__table_d14861e1_d14862e1_d14863e1__entry__1\">0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ene1665703131995__table_d14861e1_d14862e1_d14863e1__entry__2\">The bind name was successfully\n                        retrieved</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ene1665703131995__table_d14861e1_d14862e1_d14863e1__entry__1\">1</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ene1665703131995__table_d14861e1_d14862e1_d14863e1__entry__2\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">Field</var> is not a valid field\n                        name. It might be misspelled or ambiguous.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ene1665703131995__topic_d85527e1_d85528e1_d85529e1_d85530e1_d85531e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1017046e153\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ene1665703131995__d5947e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">yrtl</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ene1665703131995__topic_d85532e1_d85533e1_d85534e1_d85535e1_d85536e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1017046e166\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ene1665703131995__p_d120230e1_d120231e1_d120232e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetbind</code> returns the so-called\n            ‘internal bind name’ of the specified field. This is a string consisting of one to five\n            digits, so your buffer needs to be 6 bytes in length. Using the internal bind name is\n            never mandatory, but it is more efficient than using the field name when you call\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufget</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufgetc</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufput</code>,\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufputi</code>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufputc</code> repeatedly to get information\n            about the same field.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ene1665703131995__p_d120233e1_d120234e1_d120235e1\">See the description of <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufput</code> for\n            example code using <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetbind</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ene1665703131995__section_a15_gwz_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1017046e201\">Example: ufput, ufputc, ufputi, and ugetbind</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example reads a graphics file from disk in chunks of 5000\n            bytes, and transfers the contents to the Uniface image field IMGFIELD. This field should\n            be defined in the form as:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ene1665703131995__ul_b15_gwz_zvb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ene1665703131995__li_d45185e1_d45186e1_d45187e1\">Data Type—Image (database)</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ene1665703131995__li_d45188e1_d45189e1_d45190e1\">Widget Type—Picture </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ene1665703131995__li_d45191e1_d45192e1_d45193e1\">Interface—R*</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">Note that, in the calls to <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufput</code> and\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufputc</code>, we specify a negative length, because we are not sure if\n            there is more data until we have read the entire file. Once we have read all the file,\n            we issue a final call to <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufputc</code> with length zero to denote that the\n            transfer is complete.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104ene1665703131995_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"ene1665703131995__codeblock_x3w_3wz_zvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;\nEXPORT void GETIMAGE ()\n{\nFILE* fp;\nshort len;\nchar buf[5000];\nchar bindname[80];\n\n/* Use bindname for efficiency */\nugetbind(\"IMGFIELD\", bindname);\n/* Open binary read mode */\nfp = fopen(\"d:\\\\temp\\\\mypicture.jpg\", \"rb\");\nlen = fread(buf, 1, 5000, fp); /* Read first chunk */\nufput(bindname, buf, -len); /* Assume more to come */\nwhile (len &gt; 0)\n{\nlen = fread(buf, 1, 5000, fp); /* Read next chunk */\nif ( len &gt; 0 ) /* Assume more to come */\nufputc(bindname, buf, -len);\n}\nufputc(bindname, buf, 0); /* Tell Uniface it's done */\nfclose(fp); /* and close file */\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lyr1665703131793.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ufget</a><p>Get data from a field displayed in a Uniface component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wxh1665703131924.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ufgetc</a><p>Get additional data from a field displayed in a Uniface component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cyq1665703132133.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ufput</a><p>Copy data from a program buffer into a Uniface field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zhm1665703132396.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ufputc</a><p>Copy additional data from a program buffer into a Uniface field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dxp1665703132477.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ufputi</a><p>Copy data from a program buffer into a Uniface field as if the switch /init were used.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527218\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527218\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ugetbind Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 30, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Get the internal bind name of a Uniface field. Explain this code int ugetbind (unsigned char*fieldname,unsigned char*bindname); Copy Parameters fieldname Name of a field in your component. To resolve ambiguity, you can qualify the field name with an entity name, for example, fieldname . entity . bindname String that receives the internal bind name. This buffer should be at least 6 bytes in length. Return Values Table 1. Values returned by ugetbind Value Meaning 0 The bind name was successfully retrieved 1 Field is not a valid field name. It might be misspelled or ambiguous. Use Library: yrtl Description ugetbind returns the so-called ‘internal bind name’ of the specified field. This is a string consisting of one to five digits, so your buffer needs to be 6 bytes in length. Using the internal bind name is never mandatory, but it is more efficient than using the field name when you call ufget , ufgetc , ufput , ufputi , and ufputc repeatedly to get information about the same field. See the description of ufput for example code using ugetbind . Example: ufput, ufputc, ufputi, and ugetbind The following example reads a graphics file from disk in chunks of 5000 bytes, and transfers the contents to the Uniface image field IMGFIELD. This field should be defined in the form as: Data Type—Image (database) Widget Type—Picture Interface—R* Note that, in the calls to ufput and ufputc , we specify a negative length, because we are not sure if there is more data until we have read the entire file. Once we have read all the file, we issue a final call to ufputc with length zero to denote that the transfer is complete. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> #include <stdio.h> EXPORT void GETIMAGE () { FILE* fp; short len; char buf[5000]; char bindname[80]; /* Use bindname for efficiency */ ugetbind(\"IMGFIELD\", bindname); /* Open binary read mode */ fp = fopen(\"d:\\\\temp\\\\mypicture.jpg\", \"rb\"); len = fread(buf, 1, 5000, fp); /* Read first chunk */ ufput(bindname, buf, -len); /* Assume more to come */ while (len > 0) { len = fread(buf, 1, 5000, fp); /* Read next chunk */ if ( len > 0 ) /* Assume more to come */ ufputc(bindname, buf, -len); } ufputc(bindname, buf, 0); /* Tell Uniface it's done */ fclose(fp); /* and close file */ } Copy Related Links ufget Get data from a field displayed in a Uniface component. ufgetc Get additional data from a field displayed in a Uniface component. ufput Copy data from a program buffer into a Uniface field. ufputc Copy additional data from a program buffer into a Uniface field. ufputi Copy data from a program buffer into a Uniface field as if the switch /init were used. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}